      <bioghist id="aspace_da26294e956d8877834dfa393f1ab958">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>A. Page Browne, Jr. was born in Boston, Massachusetts on May 23, 1932. He received his B.S. from Yale University in 1955. He became Assistant Treasurer and later Assistant Vice President of the International Banking Department of the Bankers Trust Company. He specialized in foreign trade and was among the first bankers to travel to the Soviet bloc countries to promote economic ties with the United States. During his travels, Browne observed the economic conditions of the communist countries and worked to increase East-West trade by meeting with representatives from foreign and national banks of Yugoslavia, Romania and Poland.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_930d86c2cdfdddbcf75751c972a6916b">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers are comprised of reports, research material, memoranda, correspondence, and newspaper clippings created and compiled by A. Page Browne Jr. as he traveled and conducted business in Hungary, Poland, Yugoslavia, Romania, and the Soviet Union. The collection documents Browne's business affairs and his reflections on economic conditions in the eastern bloc countries during the 1960s.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
